-- Correa’s Cabinet to Boycott Ecuadorean Press, Spokesman Says
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-06-13T18:15:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/correa-s-cabinet-to-boycott-ecuadorean-press-spokesman-says.html
Ecuador’s President Rafael Correa
and his cabinet will boycott any private media critical of the
government, favoring the state-controlled press instead,
Communication Secretary Fernando Alvarado said today.  “The government’s decision to not concede interviews to
private media is based on consistency with the political
discourse of the president,” Alvarado said, according to a
statement published in the president’s official gazette.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in  Quito  at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 